Package com.cafean.client.values

Interface Accessor

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    SharedReal
    public interface Accessor
    This interface acts as a handle to a model variable that can be modified by parametric streams. It provides everything required by the stream type to display the variable, retrieve an identifier used to find the variable, and modify it during export. This interface can be implemented directly by objects that represent a single value or by a proxy class that represents one or more values in one or more components.

    • Method Detail

      • getAccessorID

        java.lang.String getAccessorID()
        Gets a unique identifier for the underlying variable.The value must be unique within the parent model. The identifier must be consistent with the AbstractNumericsModel's implementation of findAccessor. Implementations may not return null or the empty String.

        Accessor IDs have an upper length limit of 1024 characters, but should generally be as small as reasonable.

        Returns:
        a unique identifier for the underlying variable

      • getAccessorName

        java.lang.String getAccessorName()
        Gets the name of the underlying variable.This value need not be unique, and may be arbitrarily defined by the user.
        Returns:
        the name of the underlying variable

      • getAccessorType

        java.lang.String getAccessorType()
        Gets the name of the parent AccessorType for this variable. Implementations should return the same value as calling getName() on the parent type.
        Returns:
        name of the parent AccessorType for this variable

      • getAccessorShortType

        java.lang.String getAccessorShortType()
        Gets the name of the accessor type as a short description suitable for use in ASCII files. The value should be singular. For example, "Sensitivity Coefficient" might return "Sens. Coef".
        Returns:
        the name of the accessor type as a short description suitable for use in ASCII files

      • isAccessorSingleValue

        boolean isAccessorSingleValue()
        Determines whether the Accessor represents a single nominal value, returned by getAccessorNominalValue(). When false, getAccessorNominalValue() must still return a non-null value in the units for the values represented by the Accessor.
        Returns:
        true when the accessor represents a single nominal value.

      • getAccessorRangeDesc

        java.lang.String getAccessorRangeDesc()
        Gets a short description of the values represented by this instance when isAccessorSingleValue() returns false. The result must be non-null and should fit inside a table cell or ASCII table column. This method need not return a valid description when isAccessorSingleValue returns true.
        Returns:
        a description of values represented by this instance

      • getAccessorModifiedValue

        CReal getAccessorModifiedValue​(CReal variate,
                               ApplyRule rule)
        Gets a newly instantiated copy of the original model value after being modified by a given variate with the provided rule.This method must be consistent with adjustAccessorValue.Implementation that return false from isAccessorSingleValue but still represent a single value (such as in implementations that always replace the original value while setting a type flag with the application rule) may still return a value from this method. Implementations may return null if isAccessorSingleValue returns False. Otherwise, this method must return a non-null value.
        Parameters:
        variate - the variate to the applied the the accessed value
        rule - the method in which the variate will be applied to the accessed value
        Returns:
        the CReal accessed value modified by the variate using the provided ApplyRule rule.

      • getAccessorRules

        java.util.EnumSet<ApplyRule> getAccessorRules()
        Gets the set of rules that may be applied to this Accessor. Most implementations should return the entire set, using 
        return EnumSet.allOf(ApplyRule.class);
        . If the Accessor has restrictions, indicate which modes are not supported by returning which rules are allowed.
        Returns:
        the set of rules that may be applied to this Accessor
